ownedComment.body: This attribute identifies a list of base object instances for the subtrees to be retrieved. It is a list of serialized MTOSI names. If the list is left empty then all the nodes at the top of the MTOSI instance tree are selected (i.e., all MDs, TMDs, inter-MD-TLs, and OSs are selected). Specification of the baseInstanceList does not select any objects in and of itself. In order to select specific objects, one needs to specify the IncludedObjectTypes. The ";" is used as a separator, and "=" is used to associate a value with a type of object. For example, MD=md1;ME=ME123;EH=ACME7 identifies an equipment holder within managed element ME123 within management domain md1. The relative name of the equipment holder is ACME7. The following abbreviations are used for the object type names: MD - management domain ME - managed element EH - equipment holder EQ - equipment PTP - physical termination point FTP - floating termination point CTP - connection termination point TPPool - termination point pool EPGP - equipment protection group PGP - protection group SNC - subnetwork connection MLSN - multi layer subnetwork TL - topological link OS - operations system TMD - transmission descriptor.
ownedComment.name: <Unnamed Comment>

ownedComment.body:
This attribute identifies the type of objects contained under the selected base object instances that are to be included in the returned inventory file. The requesting OS always have to provide at least one object. The base object itself may also be included.
For each included object type, one needs to indicate whether a. just the name, b. all the associated attributes (including the name), or c. the associated attributes and relationship pointers are to be returned for each instance.
The includedObjectTypes need to be picked such that each selected base class has a single (connected) subtree below it.
The following abbreviations are used for the object type names: MD - management domain ME - managed element EH - equipment holder EQ - equipment PTP - physical termination point FTP - floating termination point CTP - connection termination point TPPool - termination point pool EPGP - equipment protection group PGP - protection group SNC - subnetwork connection RT - route CC - cross connection MLSN - multi layer subnetwork TL - topological link OS - operations system TMD - transmission descriptor.
